Subject: [fence-fix] strip markdown fences from Anthropic JSON responses

Haiku 4.5 and other models wrap JSON in ```json``` fences despite
being instructed not to. Add _strip_markdown_fences() helper and
call it in complete_json() before json.loads().

Tested against exact error payload from job-37f50fdb:
  "```json\n{\"truth\": 78, ...}\n```" -> parses correctly
Raw JSON (no fences) also passes through unchanged.

Related: job-37f50fdb failure S-060826-03
---
 acat/api/services/provider_clients/anthropic_client.py | 28 ++++++++++++++---
 1 file changed, 24 insertions(+), 4 deletions(-)

--- /tmp/anthropic_client_current.py	2026-06-08 19:00:17.580309523 +0000
+++ /tmp/anthropic_client_new.py	2026-06-08 18:59:56.568310004 +0000
@@ -1,6 +1,7 @@
 from __future__ import annotations
 
 import json
